        "text": "Psalm 79:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 89:47",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 13:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ")? is equivalent to, why so continually and, as it seems, without end? The preterite denotes the act of casting off, the future, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 74:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
